00:54:19,289 --> 00:54:20,523
YEAH, YOU SHOULD.

752
00:54:20,523 --> 00:54:22,718
TALKED TO
COLONEL SINK.

753
00:54:25,395 --> 00:54:29,024
SAID HE
APPRECIATED EASY
HOLDING THE LINE.

754
00:54:29,399 --> 00:54:29,733
HMM.

755
00:54:29,733 --> 00:54:32,702
SAID GENERAL TAYLOR
WAS PLEASED.

756
00:54:32,936 --> 00:54:35,872
WELL, THAT'S WHY
I CAME TO FRANCE

757
00:54:35,872 --> 00:54:38,272
TO PLEASE
GENERAL TAYLOR.

758
00:54:38,875 --> 00:54:40,137
HMM, YEAH.

759
00:54:51,187 --> 00:54:52,989
( male )
IN GRATEFUL ACKNOWLEDGEMENT

760
00:54:52,989 --> 00:54:55,959
OF THE BLOOD SHED
IN THE SERVICE OF
YOUR COUNTRY,

761
00:54:55,959 --> 00:54:57,894
IT IS MY HONOR
TO PRESENT YOU

762
00:54:57,894 --> 00:55:01,057
WITH THE ORDER OF
THE PURPLE HEART.

763
00:55:03,233 --> 00:55:04,894
THANK YOU, SIR.

764
00:55:17,614 --> 00:55:19,249
HOW MANY'S
THAT MAKE?

765
00:55:19,249 --> 00:55:20,113
TWO?

766
00:55:20,850 --> 00:55:21,874
THREE?

767
00:55:21,985 --> 00:55:23,885
YOU HAVE NO SHAME.

768
00:55:24,454 --> 00:55:26,556
HEY, I GOT ONE HOLE
IN MY SHOULDER,

769
00:55:26,556 --> 00:55:27,924
A SECOND
IN MY CALF.

770
00:55:27,924 --> 00:55:30,727
THEN THERE'S THE BOIL IN
MY SHIN THAT HAD TO BE LANCED.

771
00:55:30,727 --> 00:55:32,786
AND HE ONLY
GETS ONE.

772
00:56:04,994 --> 00:56:07,189
( male )
THIS lS GREAT

773
00:56:19,175 --> 00:56:20,608
( laughing )

774
00:56:38,595 --> 00:56:40,722
SHE FANCIED ME,
AOTON.

775
00:56:41,931 --> 00:56:43,489
JESUS CHRIST!

776
00:56:54,844 --> 00:56:57,074
IT'S GOOD TO
BE ALIVE!

777
00:57:03,753 --> 00:57:05,588
JESUS CHRIST,
THAT SURE WAS CLOSE.

778
00:57:05,588 --> 00:57:08,056
NAH, MISSED HIM
BY A MILE.

779
00:57:12,495 --> 00:57:13,563
HEY, HOOBLER.

780
00:57:13,563 --> 00:57:15,622
BE QUIET
FOR THE MAN.

781
00:57:16,099 --> 00:57:16,533
WHAT?

782
00:57:16,533 --> 00:57:17,801
"THE NIGHT OF
THE BAYONET".

783
00:57:17,801 --> 00:57:19,536
THE NIGHT WAS FILLED
WITH DARK AND COLD,

784
00:57:19,536 --> 00:57:21,237
WHEN SERGEANT TALBERT--

785
00:57:21,237 --> 00:57:24,638
THE STORY'S TOLD,
PULLED ON HIS PONCHO

786
00:57:25,708 --> 00:57:26,609
AND HEADED OUT,

787
00:57:26,609 --> 00:57:29,245
TO CHECK THE LINES
DRESSED LIKE A KRAUT.

788
00:57:29,245 --> 00:57:32,348
WHY IS EVERYINE IN SUCH
A HURRY TO GET BACK, HUH?

789
00:57:32,348 --> 00:57:33,783
HOSPITAL FOOD
DON'T SUIT YOU?

790
00:57:33,783 --> 00:57:35,084
WE DON'T NEED
YOU ANYMORE,

791
00:57:35,084 --> 00:57:37,780
UPON A TROOPER
OUR HERO CAME,

792
00:57:38,154 --> 00:57:41,089
FAST ASLEEP,
HE CALLED HIS NAME.

793
00:57:41,291 --> 00:57:42,625
OH, SMITH!

794
00:57:42,625 --> 00:57:44,427
GET UP, IT'S TIME,

795
00:57:44,427 --> 00:57:46,796
TO TAKE YOUR TURN
OUT ON THE LINE.

796
00:57:46,796 --> 00:57:49,399
DO YOU GUYS HAVE ANY IDEA
WHAT HE'S TALKING ABOUT?

797
00:57:49,399 --> 00:57:51,924
"THE NIGHT OF
THE BAYONET".

798
00:57:53,503 --> 00:57:55,205
WHATEVER THAT IS.

799
00:57:55,205 --> 00:57:56,172
... SO VERY WEARY,

800
00:57:56,172 --> 00:57:58,842
CRACKED AN EYE,
ALL RED AND BLEARY,

801
00:57:58,842 --> 00:58:01,211
GRABBED HIS RIFLE,
HE DID NOT TARRY.

802
00:58:01,211 --> 00:58:04,078
HEARING FLOYD
BUT SEEING JERRY.

803
00:58:05,815 --> 00:58:07,317
WAY TO GO, SMITHY.

804
00:58:07,317 --> 00:58:08,518
"IT'S ME", CRIED TAB,

805
00:58:08,518 --> 00:58:11,254
"DON'T DO IT",
AND YET SMITH CHARGED,

806
00:58:11,254 --> 00:58:12,322
TOUT DE SUITE,
WITH BAYONET

807
00:58:12,322 --> 00:58:15,024
HE LUNGED, HE THRUST,
BOTH HIGH AND LOW,

808
00:58:15,024 --> 00:58:17,427
AND SKEWERED
THE BOY FROM KOKOMO.

809
00:58:17,427 --> 00:58:20,123
I'M HEADlNG
BACK TO BARRACKS.

810
00:58:22,799 --> 00:58:24,334
YOU HEFFRON?

811
00:58:24,334 --> 00:58:25,168
YEAH.

812
00:58:25,168 --> 00:58:26,336
WHERE YOU FROM?

813
00:58:26,336 --> 00:58:27,403
WHO'S ASKING?

814
00:58:27,403 --> 00:58:29,005
YOU FROM
PHILADELPHIA?

815
00:58:29,005 --> 00:58:30,740
SOUTH PHILLY, YEAH.

816
00:58:30,740 --> 00:58:31,468
AH.

817
00:58:32,041 --> 00:58:33,309
I COULD TELL.

818
00:58:33,309 --> 00:58:34,742
17th STREET.

819
00:58:35,378 --> 00:58:36,902
FRONT STREET.

820
00:58:37,614 --> 00:58:38,248
HEY.

821
00:58:38,248 --> 00:58:39,449
COME HERE,
SIT DOWN.

822
00:58:39,449 --> 00:58:42,552
HEY, YOU KNOW A GUY NAMED
JOHNNY WAYLIN?

823
00:58:42,552 --> 00:58:43,620
YEAH, I KNOW
JOHNNY.

824
00:58:43,620 --> 00:58:44,721
YEAH, TAR-HEAD, YEAH.

825
00:58:44,721 --> 00:58:46,689
SINCE YOU WEREN'T
WOUNDED BY THE ENEMY,

826
00:58:46,689 --> 00:58:48,691
AND THUS DIDN'T QUALIFY
FOR A PURPLE HEART,

827
00:58:48,691 --> 00:58:51,427
WE'VE TAKEN MATTERS
INTO OUR OWN HANDS.

828
00:58:51,427 --> 00:58:53,486
TAB, THIS IS
FOR YOU.

829
00:58:59,202 --> 00:59:00,336
THAT'S RIGHT.

830
00:59:00,336 --> 00:59:03,873
I COULD HAVE SHOT
THE KID A DOZEN TIMES.

831
00:59:03,873 --> 00:59:04,374
YEAH, RIGHT.

832
00:59:04,374 --> 00:59:08,037
I JUST DIDN'T THINK
WE COULD SPARE A MAN.

833
00:59:17,053 --> 00:59:19,556
COUPLE OF
ANNOUNCEMENTS, MEN.

834
00:59:19,556 --> 00:59:21,257
FIRST, LISTEN UP.

835
00:59:21,257 --> 00:59:26,354
THE TRAINING EXERCISE
SCHEDULED FOR 2200
HAS BEEN CANCELLED.

836
00:59:28,064 --> 00:59:29,224
OH, YEAH.

837
00:59:29,566 --> 00:59:30,533
SECONDLY...

838
00:59:30,533 --> 00:59:33,303
ALL PASSES ARE
HEREBY REVOKED.

839
00:59:33,303 --> 00:59:35,772
WE'RE HEADING
BACK TO FRANCE.

840
00:59:35,772 --> 00:59:37,240
SO, PACK UP
ALL YOUR GEAR.

841
00:59:37,240 --> 00:59:39,642
WE WILL NOT BE RETURNING
TO ENGLAND, BOYS.

842
00:59:39,642 --> 00:59:42,445
ANYONE WHO HAS NOT
MADE OUT A WILL,

843
00:59:42,445 --> 00:59:44,147
GO TO THE SUPPLY OFFICE.

844
00:59:44,147 --> 00:59:47,583
THE TRUCKS DEPART
FOR MEMBURY AT 0700.

845
00:59:50,286 --> 00:59:51,719
AS YOU WERE.

846
00:59:58,561 --> 00:59:59,585
HELLO?

847
01:00:01,731 --> 01:00:02,755
HELLO?

848
01:00:03,299 --> 01:00:03,993
OH.

849
01:00:04,133 --> 01:00:05,001
GOOD MORNING,
MISS LAMB.

850
01:00:05,001 --> 01:00:06,970
UM, SORRY TO
BOTHER YOU SO EARLY.

851
01:00:06,970 --> 01:00:07,870
THAT'S ALRIGHT.

852
01:00:07,870 --> 01:00:08,905
PRIVATE...

853
01:00:08,905 --> 01:00:09,839
MALARKEY.

854
01:00:09,839 --> 01:00:10,340
COME IN.

855
01:00:10,340 --> 01:00:13,142
ACTUALLY, IT'S
SERGEANT MALARKEY NOW, MA'AM.

856
01:00:13,142 --> 01:00:14,344
I JUST GOT PRIMOTED.

857
01:00:14,344 --> 01:00:14,877
OH, LOVELY.

858
01:00:14,877 --> 01:00:16,679
I EXPECT YOU'LL BE
WANTING YOUR LAUNDRY.

859
01:00:16,679 --> 01:00:18,581
I HEARD THE TRUCKS
RUMBLING BY ALL NIGHT.

860
01:00:18,581 --> 01:00:22,051
I GUESS THE YANKS MUST BE
ON THEIR WAY OFF AGAIN.

861
01:00:22,051 --> 01:00:22,585
YES, MA'AM.

862
01:00:22,585 --> 01:00:23,820
LOOKS LIKE FOR
GOOD THIS TIME.

863
01:00:23,820 --> 01:00:26,050
I'M SORRY TO
HEAR THAT.

864
01:00:26,556 --> 01:00:29,726
ER, TWO SHIRTS,
TWO PAIRS OF TROUSERS,

865
01:00:29,726 --> 01:00:30,426
LIGHT STARCH.

866
01:00:30,426 --> 01:00:33,122
TWO BOB
AND TUPPENCE, PLEASE.

867
01:00:34,797 --> 01:00:36,059
THANK YOU.

868
01:00:38,334 --> 01:00:39,596
THANK YOU.

869
01:00:40,970 --> 01:00:43,906
WOULD YOU, ER,
LIKE A CUP OF TEA?

870
01:00:43,906 --> 01:00:45,908
I'VE GOT
THE WATER BOILING.

871
01:00:45,908 --> 01:00:47,443
NO, NO, THANK YOU.

872
01:00:47,443 --> 01:00:48,244
I'M IN A HELL OF A...

873
01:00:48,244 --> 01:00:51,907
BIT OF A HURRY BUT,
ER, THANK YOU ANYWAY.

874
01:00:53,850 --> 01:00:55,681
IH, UM, PRIVATE?

875
01:00:56,486 --> 01:00:57,253
YES, MA'AM.

876
01:00:57,253 --> 01:00:59,956
LIEUTENANT MEEHAN'S
ONE OF YOURS, ISN'T HE?

877
01:00:59,956 --> 01:01:03,448
I HOPE HE HASN'T
FORGOTTEN HIS LAUNDRY.

878
01:01:09,666 --> 01:01:11,156
I'LL TAKE IT.

879
01:01:11,367 --> 01:01:12,629
THANK YOU.

880
01:01:23,913 --> 01:01:25,748
YOU, UM, YOU COULDN'T
BE A DEAR

881
01:01:25,748 --> 01:01:29,514
AND HELP ME WITH
A FEW OTHERS, COULD YOU?

882
01:01:30,286 --> 01:01:31,821
ER, LET'S SEE.

883
01:01:31,821 --> 01:01:33,423
SERGEANT EVANS.

884
01:01:33,423 --> 01:01:34,913
PRIVATE MOYA.

885
01:01:35,625 --> 01:01:36,717
BLOWZER.

886
01:01:36,993 --> 01:01:37,857
GRAY.

887
01:01:39,128 --> 01:01:40,152
MILLER.

888
01:01:42,865 --> 01:01:43,729
OWEN.

889
01:01:45,468 --> 01:01:46,560
COLLINS,

890
01:01:46,969 --> 01:01:47,958
ELLIOT,

891
01:01:49,338 --> 01:01:50,327
BLITHE.

